gomodel:SYNGO_500  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Biochemical fractionation of mouse forebrain followed by Western blot analysis reveals the presence of phosphorylated PAK1 in the PSD fraction.\n\n29/8/2017 Pim\n- Authors state: \"p-PAK predominantly localizes in the cell soma, dendrites, and dendritic spines while it is largely excluded from the axons and boutons of mature cortical neurons\" based on IF data.. Experimental description: C57BL6 genetic background. Literal; \"Mouse forebrains were homogenized in RIPA buffer...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" ;
